#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
ZenSnore Standalone Recorder (2 buttons + 3 LEDs) with software-only corruption mitigation.


LED states:
- Boot / idle armed: ALL ON (green+yellow+red)
- Recording: GREEN only
- Stopped (after recording): YELLOW only (until Button1 pressed)
- Shutdown warning: RED blink, then safe shutdown


Buttons (BCM):
- Button1 (GPIO5): safe shutdown
- Button2 (GPIO6): toggle recording start/stop


Files per session in ./runs/run_YYYYmmdd_HHMMSS/:
- airflow.csv     @100 Hz: t_ns, pressure_kpa_zeroed
- ppg.csv         @100 Hz: t_ns, RED, IR, fs_eff_hz, ir_dc, red_dc, ir_ac_rms, red_ac_rms, R
                  (1 Hz columns filled every 100th row; others blank)
- audio.wav       @8 kHz: 32-bit PCM container
- audio_freq.csv  ~1 Hz: t_ns, rms, peak_hz
- run_metadata.json
"""


